1) Epoch

An Epoch means:

One complete pass of the entire dataset through the neural network

Simple Meaning

If ANN studies all training data once:

= 1 Epoch

=============


Real-Time Example 

Suppose:

You have 100 pages to study

If you read all 100 pages once:

1 Epoch

Reading all pages again:

2 Epochs

==================

2) Batch Size

Batch Size means:

Number of training samples processed at one time

Instead of sending all data together, ANN divides data into small groups.

Example

Suppose dataset has:

1000 images

Batch size:

100

Then ANN processes:

100 images at a time

=======

Real-Time Example 

Suppose waiter serves food.

Total plates = 100
Carries 10 plates at a time

Here:

Batch Size = 10

=========

3) Iteration

Iteration means:

One update of weights using one batch

Each batch processing = one iteration.

Formula Relation

Iterations=

Dataset Size / Batch Size

======

Example

Suppose:

Dataset = 1000 images
Batch size = 100

Then:

Iterations = 1000 / 100 = 10

Meaning:

10 iterations complete 1 epoch

===========

Full Connection

Dataset
   ↓
Divide into batches
   ↓
Each batch processed = 1 Iteration
   ↓
All batches completed = 1 Epoch

==============

Complete Real-Time Example 

Suppose:

Teacher has 1000 answer sheets
========
Batch Size
Teacher checks:
100 papers at a time
========
Iteration
Checking one batch of 100 papers:
1 Iteration
========
Epoch
Checking all 1000 papers once:
1 Epoch
========









